It is understood that farm workers found the dehorned animals on Wednesday night and alerted authorities. JOHANNESBURG - Three rhinos have been killed at a farm in Cumberland outside Lephalale in Limpopo.It is understood that farm workers found the dehorned animals on Wednesday night and alerted authorities.Police are searching for the criminals.Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says: Our provincial tracking team has launched a massive manhunt together with the Cumberland police outside Lephalale for a group of rhino poachers. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)